a:17:{s:4:"name";s:15:"Retin-A Gel 0,1";s:11:"small_descr";s:38:"Retin-A Gel is used for treating acne.";s:14:"small_descr_de";s:51:"Retin-A Gel wird zur Behandlung von Akne verwendet.";s:14:"small_descr_fr";s:46:"Retin-A Gel est utilisé pour traiter l'acné.";s:14:"small_descr_es";s:43:"Retin-A Gel es utilizado para tratar acné.";s:14:"small_descr_it";s:37:"Retin-A Gel si usa per trattare acne.";s:10:"full_descr";s:3934:"<p><strong>Drug Name</strong><br /><br />Retin-A Gel 0.1% (Tretinoin)</p><p><strong>Drug Uses</strong><br /><br />Retin-A Gel is used for treating acne. It may also be used for other conditions as determined by your doctor.</p><p><strong>How to use</strong><br /><br />Use Retin-A Gel as directed by your doctor. Check the label on the medicine for exact dosing instructions.&nbsp;<br /> Retin-A Gel is for external use only. <br /> Apply a thin film of medicine to the affected area. Rub in gently. <br /> Remove all cosmetics with a mild soap before applying Retin-A Gel. Gently dry the area. Wait 20 to 30 minutes to make sure that your skin is completely dry. <br /> Wash your hands immediately after using Retin-A Gel. <br /> If you miss a dose of Retin-A Gel, skip the missed dose and go back to your regular dosing schedule. <br /><br /><strong>Drug Class and Mechanism</strong><br /><br />Retin-A Gel is a vitamin A derivative. How it exerts its beneficial effects against acne is not fully known. Tretinoin appears to increase skin-cell turnover and to reduce the tendency for skin cells to stick together. This reduces the formation of acne and allows quicker healing of acne that does develop.</p><p><strong>Missed Dose</strong><br /><br />If you miss a dose of Retin-A Gel, skip the missed dose and go back to your regular dosing schedule. Do not use 2 doses at once.</p><p><strong>Storage</strong><br /><br />Store Retin-A Gel at room temperature, between 59 and 80 degrees F (15 and 26 degrees C). Store in a tightly closed container. Store away from heat and light. Keep Retin-A Gel out of the reach of children and away from pets.</p><p><strong>SAFETY INFORMATION</strong></p><p><strong>Warnings/Precautions</strong><br /><br />Do NOT use Retin-A Gel if you are allergic to any ingredient in Retin-A Gel.<br /> Contact your doctor or health care provider right away if any of these apply to you.<br /><br /> Before using Retin-A Gel:<br /> Some medical conditions may interact with Retin-A Gel. Tell your doctor or pharmacist if you have any medical conditions, especially if any of the following apply to you: <br /> if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or are breast-feeding <br /> if you are taking any prescription or nonprescription medicine, herbal preparation, or dietary supplement <br /> if you have allergies to medicines, foods, or other substances <br /> if you have eczema, an abnormally high white blood cell count, or a sunburn <br /> Some MEDICINES MAY INTERACT with Retin-A Gel. Because little, if any, of Retin-A Gel is absorbed into the blood, the risk of it interacting with another medicine is low.<br /><br /> Ask your health care provider if Retin-A Gel may interact with other medicines that you take. Check with your health care provider before you start, stop, or change the dose of any medicine.</p><p><strong>SIDE EFFECTS</strong></p><p><strong>Possible Side Effects</strong><br /><br />All medicines may cause side effects, but many people have no, or minor, side effects. Check with your doctor if any of these most COMMON side effects persist or become bothersome:<br /> Redness, peeling at application site; sensitivity to sunlight; skin irritation; warmth or stinging at application site.<br /><br /> Seek medical attention right away if any of these SEVERE side effects occur:<br /> Severe allergic reactions (rash; hives; itching; difficulty breathing; tightness in the chest; swelling of the mouth, face, lips, or tongue); severe redness, peeling, swelling, blistering, or crusting of the skin.</p><p><strong>More Information</strong><br /><br />If you have any questions about Retin-A Gel, please talk with your doctor, pharmacist, or other health care provider.<br /> Retin-A Gel is to be used only by the patient for whom it is prescribed. Do not share it with other people. <br /> If your symptoms do not improve or if they become worse, check with your doctor.</p>";s:13:"full_descr_de";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_fr";s:12744:"<p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><strong><span class="hps">Nom du M&eacute;dicament</span></strong><br /><br /></span>Retin-A Gel 0,1%<span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps atn"> (</span><span>tr&eacute;tino&iuml;ne</span><span>)</span></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><strong><span class="hps alt-edited">Utilisation du Drogue</span></strong></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">Retin</span><span class="atn">-</span><span>A-Gel</span> <span class="hps">est utilis&eacute; pour traiter</span> <span class="hps">l'acn&eacute;</span><span>.</span> <span class="hps">Il peut &eacute;galement</span> <span class="hps">&ecirc;tre utilis&eacute;</span> <span class="hps">pour d'autres conditions</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">comme est d&eacute;termin&eacute; par votre</span> <span class="hps">m&eacute;decin.</span></span></p><p><strong><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps alt-edited">Comment utiliser</span></span></strong></p><p>Utilisez Retin-A-Gel selon les instructions de votre m&eacute;decin. V&eacute;rifiez l'&eacute;tiquette du m&eacute;dicament pour les instructions de dosage exact.<br />Retin-A-Gel est seulement pour l'usage externe.<br />Appliquez une couche fine du m&eacute;dicament sur la zone affect&eacute;e. Frictionneez la peau doucement avec le gel.<br />Retirez tous les cosm&eacute;tiques avec un savon doux avant d'appliquer Retin-A-Gel. S&eacute;chez d&eacute;licatement la zone. Attendez 20 &agrave; 30 minutes pour vous assurer que votre peau est compl&egrave;tement s&egrave;che.<br />Lavez-vous les mains imm&eacute;diatement apr&egrave;s l'utilisation de Retin-A-Gel.<br />Si vous manquez une dose de Retin-A-Gel, sautez la dose oubli&eacute;e et reprenez votre programme de dosage r&eacute;gulier.</p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><strong><span class="hps">Classe de drogue</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">et m&eacute;canisme d'action</span></strong></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps atn">Retin-</span><span>A-Gel</span> <span class="hps">est un</span> <span class="hps">d&eacute;riv&eacute; de vitamine A</span><span>.</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">Ce n'est pas connu comment</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">il montre</span> <span class="hps">ses</span> <span class="hps">effets b&eacute;n&eacute;fiques contre</span> <span class="hps">l'acn&eacute;</span><span>.</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">Tr&eacute;tino&iuml;ne</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">augmente</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">le renouvellement des cellules de la peau</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">et</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">r&eacute;duit</span> <span class="hps">la tendance des</span> <span class="hps">cellules de la peau</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">&agrave; s'agglutiner. </span></span><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">Cela permet de r&eacute;duire</span> <span class="hps">la formation</span> <span class="hps">de l'acn&eacute; et</span> <span class="hps">permet</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">acc&eacute;l&eacute;rer la gu&eacute;rison</span> <span class="hps">de l'acn&eacute;</span><span class="hps alt-edited">.</span></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><strong><span class="hps alt-edited">Dose oubli&eacute;e</span></strong><br /><br /> </span><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">Si vous</span> <span class="hps">manquez une dose de</span> <span class="hps atn">Retin-</span><span>A-Gel</span><span>, sautez la</span> <span class="hps">dose oubli&eacute;e et</span> <span class="hps">reprenez votre</span> <span class="hps">programme de dosage r&eacute;gulier</span><span>.</span> <span class="hps">N'utilisez pas 2</span> <span class="hps">doses &agrave; la fois</span><span>.</span></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><strong><span class="hps alt-edited">Conservation</span></strong><br /><br /> <span class="hps alt-edited">Gardez</span> <span class="hps">Retin-A</span> </span><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">gel </span></span><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">&agrave; la temp&eacute;rature ambiante</span><span>,</span> <span class="hps">entre 59 et</span> <span class="hps">80 degr&eacute;s</span> <span class="hps">F (15 et</span> <span class="hps">26 degr&eacute;ss</span> <span class="hps">F (15 et</span> <span class="hps">26 degr</span> <span class="hps">C</span><span>)</span><span>.</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">Conservez dans une</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">casse ferm&eacute;</span><span>.</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">Conservez loin</span> <span class="hps">de la chaleur</span> <span class="hps">et de la lumi&egrave;re</span><span>.</span> <span class="hps">Gardez</span> <span class="hps">Retin-A</span> <span class="hps">gel</span> <span class="hps">hors de la port&eacute;e</span> <span class="hps">des enfants</span> <span class="hps">et loin des</span> <span class="hps">animaux.<br /></span></span></p><p><strong>RENSEIGNEMENTS DE S&Eacute;CURIT&Eacute;</strong></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><strong><span class="hps">Mises en garde /</span> <span class="hps">Pr&eacute;cautions</span></strong><br /><br /> <span class="hps alt-edited">N'utilisez pas</span> <span class="hps atn">Retin-</span><span class="alt-edited">A Gel</span> <span class="hps">si vous &ecirc;tes allergique</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">&agrave; un ingr&eacute;dient de</span> <span class="hps atn">Retin-</span><span class="alt-edited">A Gel</span><span>.</span><br /> <span class="hps">Contactez votre m&eacute;decin</span> <span class="hps">imm&eacute;diatement si l'un</span> <span class="hps">de</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">ces cas s'applique</span> <span class="hps">&agrave; vous.</span></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps alt-edited">Avant l'utilisation de</span> <span class="hps atn">Retin-</span><span class="alt-edited">A Gel</span><span>:</span><br /> <span class="hps alt-edited">Certaines conditions m&eacute;dicales peuvent</span> <span class="hps">interagir avec</span> <span class="hps atn">Retin-</span><span class="alt-edited">A Gel</span><span>.</span> <span class="hps">Dites &agrave; votre</span> <span class="hps">m&eacute;decin ou &agrave;</span> <span class="hps">votre pharmacien si vous</span> <span class="hps">avez des conditions m&eacute;dicales</span> <span class="hps">surtout si une des</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">suivantes s'applique &agrave;</span> <span class="hps">vous:</span></span></p><ul><li><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">si vous &ecirc;tes enceinte</span><span class="alt-edited">, envisagez de devenir</span> <span class="hps">enceinte ou</span> <span class="hps">allaitez</span></span></li><li><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">si vous</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">prenez une prescription</span> <span class="hps">ou les m&eacute;dicaments</span> <span class="hps">en vente libre</span><span class="alt-edited">, une pr&eacute;paration</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">d'herbes </span> <span class="hps">ou des suppl&eacute;ments alimentaires</span></span></li><li><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">si vous</span> <span class="hps">avez les allergies</span> <span class="hps">aux m&eacute;dicaments</span><span class="alt-edited">, aliments ou</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">autres substances</span></span></li><li><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">si</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">vous avez l'ecz&eacute;ma</span><span class="alt-edited">, le taux</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">anormalement &eacute;lev&eacute;</span> <span class="hps">de globules blancs</span> <span class="hps">ou</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">les coups de soleil</span></span></li></ul><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">Certains m&eacute;dicaments peuvent interagir</span> <span class="hps atn">avec Retin-</span><span class="alt-edited">A Gel</span><span>.</span> <span class="hps">Parce que</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">un peu</span> <span class="hps">de Retin</span><span class="atn">-</span><span class="alt-edited">A Gel</span> <span class="hps">est</span> <span class="hps">absorb&eacute; dans le sang</span> <span class="hps">le risque de</span> <span class="hps">l'interaction avec</span> <span class="hps">un autre m&eacute;dicament</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">est bas.</span></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">Demandez &agrave; votre</span> <span class="hps">m&eacute;decin si</span> <span class="hps atn">Retin-</span><span class="alt-edited">A Gel</span> <span class="hps">peut interagir</span> <span class="hps">avec d'autres m&eacute;dicaments</span> <span class="hps">que vous prenez.</span> <span class="hps">V&eacute;rifiez aupr&egrave;s de votre</span> <span class="hps">m&eacute;decin avant de commencer</span><span class="alt-edited">, abandonner ou</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">modifier la dose d'un</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">m&eacute;dicament.</span></span></p><p><strong>LES EFFETS SECONDAIRES</strong></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><strong><span class="hps">Effets secondaires possibles</span></strong><br /><br /> <span class="hps alt-edited">Tout les m&eacute;dicaments peuvent</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">causer les effets secondaires</span> <span class="hps">mais beaucoup de gens</span> <span class="hps">n'ont pas, ou</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">ont des effets</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">secondaires mineures.</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">V&eacute;rifiez avec votre </span></span><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">m&eacute;decin si</span> <span class="hps">un de ces effets</span> <span class="hps">ind&eacute;sirables les plus courants</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">persiste ou devient g&ecirc;nant</span><span>:</span></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps alt-edited">La rougeur, la rudesse</span> <span class="hps">au site d'application</span><span class="alt-edited">; la sensibilit&eacute; &agrave; la</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">lumi&egrave;re du soleil;</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">l'irritation de la peau</span><span>;</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">la chaleur ou</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">le picotement au</span> <span class="hps">site d'application</span><span>.</span></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps alt-edited">Consultez un m&eacute;decin</span> <span class="hps">imm&eacute;diatement si</span> <span class="hps">un de ces effets</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">secondaires graves se produit</span><span>:</span></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps alt-edited">Les r&eacute;actions</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">allergiques s&eacute;v&egrave;res (l'&eacute;ruption cutan&eacute;e</span><span class="alt-edited">, l'urticaire,</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">la d&eacute;mangeaison</span><span class="alt-edited">, la difficult&eacute; &agrave; respirer</span><span class="alt-edited">, la sensation d'oppression</span> <span class="hps">dans la</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">poitrine, l'enflure</span> <span class="hps">de la</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">bouche, du visage</span><span class="alt-edited">, des l&egrave;vres</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">ou de la langue)</span><span class="alt-edited">,  la peau rouge, enfl&eacute;e, cloqu&eacute;e ou &eacute;cailleuse</span> <span class="hps">ou</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">l'exfoliation.</span></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><strong><span class="hps atn alt-edited">Information additive</span></strong></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">Si vous avez des</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">questions sur utilisation de</span> <span class="hps atn">Retin-</span><span class="alt-edited">A Gel</span> <span class="hps alt-edited"> parlez</span> <span class="hps">&agrave; votre m&eacute;decin</span><span class="hps">.</span><br /> <span class="hps atn">Retin-</span><span class="alt-edited">A Gel</span> <span class="hps">doit &ecirc;tre utilis&eacute;</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">seulement par le patient</span> <span class="hps">pour</span> <span class="hps">qui il est prescrit</span> <span class="hps alt-edited">Ne le partagez pas</span> <span class="hps">avec d'autres personnes.</span></span></p><p><span id="result_box" lang="fr"><span class="hps">Si vos sympt&ocirc;mes</span> <span class="hps">ne s'am&eacute;liorent pas ou</span> <span class="hps">s'ils s'aggravent</span> <span class="hps">consultez votre m&eacute;decin.</span></span></p>";s:13:"full_descr_es";s:4757:"<p><strong>Nombre del medicamento</strong></p><p>Retin-A Gel 0,1% (tretino&iacute;na)</p><p><strong><span id="result_box" class="short_text" lang="es"><span class="hps">Usos </span></span>del medicamento</strong></p><p>Retin-A Gel es usado para tratar el acn&eacute;. Puede ser tambi&eacute;n usado para otras condiciones seg&uacute;n las indicaciones del m&eacute;dico.</p><p><strong>Como usar</strong></p><p>Utilice Retin-A Gel como es indicado por el m&eacute;dico. Revise la etiqueta del medicamento para la dosificaci&oacute;n exacta.<br />Retin-A Gel es solamente para el uso externo<br />Aplique una capa delgada de medicamento sobre la zona afectada. Frote suavemente.</p><p>Elimine todos los cosm&eacute;ticos con un jab&oacute;n suave antes de aplicar Retin-A Gel. Seque suavemente el &aacute;rea. Espere de 20 a 30 minutos para asegurarse de que la piel es completamente seca.<br />L&aacute;ve las manos inmediatamente despu&eacute;s de usar Retin-A Gel.<br />Si olvida una dosis de Retin-A Gel, omita la dosis olvidada y vuelva a su horario regular de dosificaci&oacute;n.</p><p><strong>Clase de medicamento y Mecanismo</strong></p><p>Retin-A Gel es un derivado de la vitamina A. No conocido totalmente c&oacute;mo ejerce sus efectos beneficiosos contra el acn&eacute;. Tretino&iacute;na aumenta la renovaci&oacute;n de las c&eacute;lulas de la piel y para reduce la tendencia de las c&eacute;lulas de la piel a pegarse. Esto reduce la formaci&oacute;n de acn&eacute; y permite la r&aacute;pida cicatrizaci&oacute;n de acn&eacute; que se desarrolla.</p><p><strong>Dosis olvidada</strong></p><p>Si olvida una dosis de Retin-A Gel, omita la dosis olvidada y vuelva a su  horario regular. No utilice 2 dosis al mismo tiempo.</p><p><strong>Almacenamiento</strong></p><p>Almacene Retin-A Gel a temperatura ambiente, entre 59 y 80 grados F (15 y 26 grados C). Almacene en un envase herm&eacute;ticamente cerrado.&nbsp; Almacene lejos del calor y de la luz. Almacene Retin-A Gel fuera del alcance de ni&ntilde;os y animales dom&eacute;sticos.</p><p><strong>INFORMACI&Oacute;N DE SEGURIDAD</strong></p><p><strong>Advertencias/Precauciones</strong></p><p>NO use Retin-A Gel si usted es al&eacute;rgico a cualquier ingrediente de Retin-A Gel.<br />Contacte con su m&eacute;dico inmediatamente si alguno de estos casos aplica a Usted.</p><p><strong>Antes de usar Retin-A Gel:</strong></p><p>Algunas condiciones m&eacute;dicas pueden interactuar con Retin-A Gel. D&iacute;ga a su m&eacute;dico o farmac&eacute;utico si tiene alguna condici&oacute;n m&eacute;dica, especialmente alguno de los casos siguientes:</p><ul><li>si est&aacute; embarazada, planea caer embarazada o si amamanta</li><li>si Usted toma cualquiera prescripci&oacute;n o medicamento sin receta, la preparaci&oacute;n a base de hierbas o suplemento diet&eacute;tico</li><li>si Usted tiene alergias a medicamentos, alimentos o otras sustancias</li><li>si Usted tiene eczema, un nivel de gl&oacute;bulos blancos anormalmente alto, o una quemadura de sol</li></ul><p>Algunos medicamentos pueden interactuar con Retin-A Gel. Porque una cantidad poca, si alguna, de Retin-A Gel se absorbe en la sangre, el riesgo de la interacci&oacute;n con otro medicamento es bajo.</p><p>Pregunte a su m&eacute;dico si Retin-A Gel puede interactuar con otros medicamentos que toma. Consulte con su m&eacute;dico antes de iniciar, detener o cambiar la dosis de un medicamento.</p><p><strong>EFECTOS SECUNDARIOS</strong></p><p><strong>Efectos secundarios posibles</strong></p><p>Todos los medicamentos pueden causar efectos secundarios, pero muchas personas no tienen, o tienen efectos secundarios menores. Consulte con su m&eacute;dico si cualquier de estos efectos secundarios m&aacute;s comunes persiste o se vuelve molesto:<br />Enrojecimiento, descamaci&oacute;n en el lugar de aplicaci&oacute;n, sensibilidad a la luz del sol, irritaci&oacute;n de la piel, calor o escozor en el lugar de aplicaci&oacute;n.</p><p>Busque atenci&oacute;n m&eacute;dica inmediatamente si alguno de estos efectos secundarios graves ocurre:<br />Las reacciones al&eacute;rgicas graves (erupci&oacute;n cut&aacute;nea, urticaria, picaz&oacute;n, dificultad para respirar, opresi&oacute;n en el pecho, hinchaz&oacute;n de la boca, cara, labios o lengua), enrojecimiento, descamaci&oacute;n, hinchaz&oacute;n, ampollas o costras en la piel.</p><p><strong>M&aacute;s Informaci&oacute;n</strong></p><p>Si Usted tiene alguna pregunta sobre el uso de Retin-A Gel, por favor hable con su m&eacute;dico o farmac&eacute;utico.<br />Retin-A Gel debe ser utilizado solamente por el paciente para quien es recetado. No le comparta con otras personas.<br />Si sus s&iacute;ntomas no mejoran o si empeoran, consulte con su m&eacute;dico.</p>";s:13:"full_descr_it";s:0:"";s:9:"min_price";s:9:"11.273688";s:9:"pack_name";s:5:"tubes";s:4:"type";s:2:"gm";s:7:"analogs";a:7:{s:8:"Accutane";s:8:"Skincare";s:12:"Retin-A 0,05";s:8:"Skincare";s:14:"Tretinoin 0,05";s:8:"Skincare";s:15:"Tretinoin 0,025";s:8:"Skincare";s:13:"Retin-A 0,025";s:8:"Skincare";s:20:"Retino-A Cream 0,025";s:8:"Skincare";s:19:"Retino-A Cream 0,05";s:8:"Skincare";}s:18:"active_ingredients";N;s:8:"packings";a:1:{i:20;a:4:{i:4879;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"4879";s:5:"count";s:1:"3";s:6:"dosage";d:20;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"16.8264";s:4:"name";s:15:"Retin-A Gel 0,1";}i:4880;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"4880";s:5:"count";s:2:"10";s:6:"dosage";d:20;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:8:"12.25358";s:4:"name";s:15:"Retin-A Gel 0,1";}i:4881;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"4881";s:5:"count";s:2:"15";s:6:"dosage";d:20;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:8:"11.60032";s:4:"name";s:15:"Retin-A Gel 0,1";}i:4882;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"4882";s:5:"count";s:2:"20";s:6:"dosage";d:20;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:8:"11.27369";s:4:"name";s:15:"Retin-A Gel 0,1";}}}}